I'm using a workaround in python (this is the smallest "solution" I could g=
et)

--------------------------------------------------------------------
from multiprocessing import Pool
from glob import glob
from subprocess import call

def f(x):
  call(['echo','asy', '-f', 'png', '-render=3D0', x])

pool =3D Pool(processes=3D4)
pool.map(f, glob('*.asy'))
--------------------------------------------------------------------

But of course this solution dont integrate in zsh command line...

